title: S.J. girls: Ali sets Eastern scoring mark
text:
Cherokee 2, Washington Township 0: Devon Fitzpatrick and Leah Reistle each scored for the fifth-seeded visitors against the fourth-seeded Minutemaids. Tori Hampton had an assist.
TRI-COUNTY DIAMOND 
Glassboro 2, Cumberland 1: Maciana Mazzeo scored twice for the visitors. 
BURLINGTON COUNTY LEAGUE 
Northern Burlington 4, Bordentown 3: Ty Horne scored twice to lead the hosts. Alex Fitzpatrick and Kacie Walton also scored. 
Maple Shade 5, Willingboro 4: Alexis Ashman's two goals gave her team the edge on the road. Carly Dombrowski, Miranda Wyatt and Elora Marvasi each scored a goal. FIELD HOCKEY 
COLONIAL CONFERENCE 
West Deptford 4, Haddon Heights 0: Ciara Girouard had a goal and an assist to help the home team clinch the league title. Tricia Baud, Jessica McGivern and Erin McConville each scored. 
OLYMPIC CONFERENCE 
Lenape 1, Cherry Hill West 0: Kylie Bresley scored the lone goal in the second half for the visitors. Julia Rosenblatt and Macie Wolf assisted. 
Timber Creek 6, Winslow Township 0: Casey Wagner's hat trick paced her team on the road. Jacinta Davis, Jordan Virgilio and Caitlyn O'Sullivan also scored. 
TRI-COUNTY ROYAL 
Kingsway 7, Highland 0: Nichole Tuller had a hat trick to help the home team clinch the division championship. Celeste Azzari, Payton Barr, Lindsay Miller, and Taylor Acevedo each scored a goal. 
BURLINGTON COUNTY LEAGUE 
Bordentown 5, Holy Cross 4: Morgan Irons had a hat trick to for the hosts. Jenna Lucas and Cynthia Reynolds each scored a goal. CROSS-COUNTRY 
OLYMPIC CONFERENCE CHAMPIONSHIP 
Kara Bonner of Shawnee won the 3.1mile race at Rowan in a time of 18:45. Cherokee took the team title.
